  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "Active Participle (اسم الفاعل)",
      "titleArabic": "اسم الفاعل",
      "content": [
        "The active participle (اسم الفاعل) is a noun derived from a verb that describes the doer of an action. For Form I verbs (فَعَلَ), the pattern is فَاعِل.",
        "Active participles can function as nouns (a writer, a teacher) or as adjectives describing a state (sitting, standing, going)."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Form I pattern: فَاعِلٌ (e.g., كَاتِب from كَتَبَ)",
        "Feminine form: فَاعِلَة (e.g., كَاتِبَة)",
        "Plural patterns vary: كُتَّاب (writers), جَالِسُونَ (sitting ones)",
        "Can be used as a noun or adjective"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "كَاتِبٌ", "english": "writer / writing (m.)" },
        { "arabic": "ذَاهِبٌ", "english": "going (m.)" },
        { "arabic": "جَالِسٌ", "english": "sitting (m.)" },
        { "arabic": "وَاقِفٌ", "english": "standing (m.)" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Active Participle as Predicate",
      "titleArabic": "اسم الفاعل كخبر",
      "content": [
        "When used as a predicate (خبر), the active participle describes the current state of the subject. It must agree in gender and number with the subject."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "الطَّالِبُ جَالِسٌ (The student is sitting) - masculine",
        "الطَّالِبَةُ جَالِسَةٌ (The student is sitting) - feminine",
        "The active participle often indicates an ongoing or present state"
      ]
    }
  ],
